> Nothing says summer quite like outdoor eating, and these BBQ pulled chicken sandwiches are perfect for just that. Everything comes together in just 30 minutes—while you roast a side of potato wedges, you'll pickle your jalapeño, mix your coleslaw, and heat up your chicken. Pile it all onto toasted potato buns, then dig into a saucy, summery feast that's perfect whether you're dining al fresco or bringing the picnic indoors.

== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pickled Jalapeño ==

While potatoes roast, thinly slice @Jalapeño{1} into rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Toss in a #small bowl{} with half the @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Sugar{½%teaspoon}, and a @salt{pinch}.

== Coleslaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with remaining vinegar. Add @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce} and toss to thoroughly coat. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Halve @Potato Buns{2}. When potatoes have 3-5 minutes left, add buns to same baking sheet and toast until golden.

Place @BBQ Pulled Chicken{10%ounce} in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}; cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} or a #paper towel{}. Microwave until chicken is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Carefully uncover and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of pickling liquid from jalapeño to your chicken for a tangy kick!

Divide buns between plates; fill with BBQ pulled chicken and as much slaw and pickled jalapeño (draining first) as you like. Serve with potato wedges and @Ketchup{2%tablespoon} on the side for dipping.

> TIP: Serve any extra slaw alongside your sandwiches.